---
import Presentation from "../../../components/Presentation.astro";
import Divider from "../../../components/ui/Divider.astro";
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Code } from "astro-expressive-code/components";

//#region CodeSnippets
const Task1 = `let name = "Ada";

console.log("Name:", name);
`;
const Task2 = `let name = "Ada";
let age = 16;

console.log("Name:", name);
console.log("Age:", age);
`;
const Task3 = `let name = "Ada";
let age = 16;
let favoriteColor = "blue";
let favoriteNumber = 7;

console.log("Name:", name);
console.log("Age:", age);
console.log("Favorite Color:", favoriteColor);
console.log("Favorite Number:", favoriteNumber);
`;
const ExampleOutput = `Name: Ada
Age: 16
Favorite Color: blue
Favorite Number: 7`;
//#endregion
---

<Layout>
  <div class="container my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-10">
        <a href="/courses/ap-csp/" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-light mb-3">
          <i class="si-arrow-left"></i> Back
        </a>

        <h1>Activity 1.3: Variables and Console Output</h1>
        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-5" />

        <!-- Launch / Concept -->
        <section id="launch">
          <Presentation>
            <section>
              <h2>Activity 1.3</h2>
              <h3 class="text-sn-theme">Variables and Console Output</h3>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Concepts</h2>
              <p>Variables</p>
              <p>Console Output</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>What Is a Variable?</h2>
              <p>
                A <b class="text-sn-theme">variable</b> is a named container
                that holds a value, so you can refer back to it by name
                instead of retyping the value every time.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>Declaring a Variable</h2>
              <Code code={`let name = "Ada";`} frame="code" lang="javascript" showLineNumbers={false} />
              <p class="fragment">
                <b class="text-sn-theme">let</b> declares the variable,
                <b>name</b> is what we're calling it, and everything after
                the <b>=</b> is the value we're assigning to it.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>Naming Variables</h2>
              <p>
                JavaScript variable names use
                <b class="text-sn-theme">camelCase</b> &mdash; the first word
                lowercase, each word after that capitalized, no spaces or
                underscores.
              </p>
              <p class="fragment"><code>favoriteColor</code>, not <code>favorite_color</code> or <code>FavoriteColor</code>.</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>Console Output</h2>
              <p>
                <b class="text-sn-theme">console.log()</b> prints values to
                the terminal. It can take more than one thing at a time,
                separated by commas.
              </p>
              <Code code={`console.log("Age:", age);`} frame="code" lang="javascript" showLineNumbers={false} class="fragment" />
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Today's Objectives</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>Declaring variables with <code>let</code></li>
                <li>Naming variables using camelCase</li>
                <li>Printing variable values with <code>console.log()</code></li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Terms</h2>
              <div class="text-start">
                <dl>
                  <dt>Variable</dt>
                  <dd>A named container that holds a value.</dd>
                  <dt>Declaration</dt>
                  <dd>Creating a new variable, using <code>let</code>.</dd>
                  <dt>Assignment</dt>
                  <dd>Giving a variable a value, using <code>=</code>.</dd>
                  <dt>camelCase</dt>
                  <dd>JavaScript's naming convention &mdash; lowercase first word, capitalized words after.</dd>
                  <dt>console.log()</dt>
                  <dd>Prints one or more values to the terminal.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </section>
          </Presentation>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Build -->
        <section id="build">
          <h2>Build</h2>

          <p>
            Create a new JavaScript file named <b class="text-sn-theme">1-3-variables.js</b>.
          </p>

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 1: Declare Your First Variable</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Declare a variable named <code>name</code> and assign it your name, as a string.</li>
            <li>Print it with <code>console.log()</code>, including a label.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task1} frame="code" lang="javascript" title="1-3-variables.js" mark="1" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 2: Add a Second Variable</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Declare a variable named <code>age</code> and assign it your age, as a number.</li>
            <li>Print it with a label, just like <code>name</code>.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task2} frame="code" lang="javascript" title="1-3-variables.js" mark="2" ins="5" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 3: Add Two More Variables</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Declare <code>favoriteColor</code> and <code>favoriteNumber</code>, using camelCase.</li>
            <li>Print each one with a label.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task3} frame="code" lang="javascript" title="1-3-variables.js" mark="3-4" ins="8-9" />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Checkpoint -->
        <section id="checkpoint">
          <h2>Checkpoint</h2>

          <p>Verify your program works correctly.</p>

          <Code
            code={ExampleOutput}
            frame="terminal"
            lang="txt"
            showLineNumbers={false}
            title="Example Output"
          />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Reflection -->
        <section id="reflection">
          <h2>Reflection</h2>

          <p>Answer the following questions before submitting your work.</p>

          <ol>
            <li>What is a variable, and why do we give it a name instead of just typing the value directly every time?</li>
            <li>
              What naming convention did we use for names like
              <code>favoriteColor</code>? What's it called, and why do you
              think a consistent convention matters when writing code?
            </li>
            <li>
              What do you think would happen if you tried to
              <code>console.log()</code> a variable before declaring it?
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Submit -->
        <section id="submit">
          <h2>Submit</h2>

          <p>Submit the required files to the appropriate dropbox.</p>

          <h1
            class="text-center mt-5 text-sn-theme border border-primary slow-flash"
          >
            Activity Complete
          </h1>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
